General.Name: Platypus Minerals Ltd
General.Description: Platypus Minerals Limited explores and evaluates mineral properties in Australia and Peru. It primarily explores for gold, copper, and base metals. It primarily holds an option to earn a 70% interest in 13 concessions comprising the Central copper-gold project located in the Chanape area of the San Mateo Mining District in Peru; and an option to earn a 75% interest in 200 square kilometers exploration license located in the East Pilbara region of Western Australia. The company also holds an option to earn a 75% interest in the Gobbos copper-molybdenum project in Western Australia; and interest in the Pearl Bar copper-silver and Cyclops nickel-copper sulphide prospects in Western Australia. The company was formerly known as Ashburton Minerals Ltd and changed its name to Platypus Minerals Limited in October 2013. Platypus Minerals Limited is based in West Leederville, Australia.
